        <div class="site-container--body-content">
          <p class="hca-text--subhead hca-text__color--asphalt">A divider is a thin, lightweight line that can group or separate content in components and layouts.</p>
          <p class="hca-text--body-1">Dividers help organize page content and hierarchy into individual tiles.</p>
          <p class="hca-text--body-1">Full-bleed dividers emphasize separate content areas and sections that require more distinct visual separation. Alternatives to full-bleed dividers include white space, subheaders, or inset dividers.</p>
          <p class="hca-text--body-1">Image-based content in grid lists do not need dividers. Grid lists adequately separate content using white space and subheaders.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-5">
        <nav>
          <span class="hca-text--subhead">Contents:</span>
          <ul class="site-toc">
            <li class="site-toc__item"><a href="#section-specs">Specs</a></li>
